race.comment: WARRIOR BAE (5) scored a gritty maiden win third-up, before surging late for an excellent fifth over the 1550m at Murwillumbah C2 class. Kept fresh with the claim and gets every chance from the draw. ICEWATER (3) improving Frosted gelding who proved the maiden win was no fluke two-back when pushing forward for a comfortable victory over 1526m at this track. Trained locally and hard to ignore in this vein of form. KEEP IT LOKI (4) struggled with the big weights at his last two runs and set to lift on the firmer surface. This looks easier and quickly running out of chances. THUNDEROUS (9) only the one win from fifteen starts and assess on his improved seventh at Gatton two starts back. Will need everything to go right.
